Rating: 4
I brought this dish to a BBQ and it got rave reviews from all! It was an excellent contrast with smoked beef ribs and spicy fried turkey as the salsa is cool and refreshing. It's also great on its own with the mix of sweet and cool fruit and mint with the spicy vegetables. This is definitely a keeper! The only variation I did was to include both cantelope and honeydew since I like them both and wanted the different colors.